  "label": "Bafflelit Sleeping Cell",
  "description": "Bafflelit Sleeping Cell constitutes a compact bedroom carved into the tenement’s salt-cemented basalt courses, its surfaces darkened to suppress Saltharrow’s hard white glare. A recessed sleeping platform and built-in stone niches occupy one wall, their edges rounded and brine-sealed against grit. Overhead, a shuttered baffle and narrow vent flue admit controlled air through grit filters, maintaining the tenement’s even interior dimness. The floor is scored with shallow channels that guide brine wash toward a drain cut into the basalt.",
